article.headline: Southern Cal 60, Saint Mary's 49
article.story: HONOLULU -- Mike Gerrity scored 17 points and Nikola Vucevic added 15 points with seven rebounds to lead Southern California to a 60-49 win over Saint Mary's in a Diamond Head Classic semifinal game Wednesday. The Trojans (7-4) fell behind early, but took the lead for good on a Marcus Johnson basket with 11:09 left in the first half, which ignited a 19-5 USC run. The Gaels (10-2) were held to a season low in scoring and shot just 30 percent (16-for-53) from the field. USC opened the second half with a 6-0 run, which was capped by a 17-foot jumper by Vucevic to give the Trojans their largest lead at 39-23. Saint Mary's closed within 47-43 with 4:48 left on a Mickey McConnell layup, but Gerrity drained a 3-pointer on USC's next trip down the floor. McConnell had 17 points and Omar Samhan added 13 for Saint Mary's.
